===Etymology===
From {{enm}}, from {{ang}} ''[[niht]]''. Cognates include {{grc}} ''[[νύξ]]'' (nyx), {{la}} ''[[nox]]'', {{got}} ''[[𐌽𐌰𐌷𐍄𐍃]]'' (nahts), {{de}} ''[[Nacht]]'' and {{ru}} ''[[ночь]]'' (noch').

===Pronunciation===
*nīt, /naɪt/, /<tt>naIt</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[knight]], [[nite]]
*:'''Rhymes''': [[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|-aɪt]]

===Alternative spellings===
*[[nite]] (''informal'')

===Noun===
'''night''' (''plural'' [[nights]])

#The period between [[sunset]] and [[sunrise]], when the sky is dark.
#(''countable'') [[Darkness]].
#:''The cat disappeared into the night.''

====Synonyms====
*(''darkness''): [[blackness]], [[darkness]], [[gloom]], [[obscurity]], [[shadow]]

====Antonyms====
*(''period between sunset and sunrise''): [[day]]
*(''darkness''): [[brightness]], [[daylight]], [[light]]

